#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:1
msgid "VTK::WrappingPythonCore"
msgstr "VTK::WrappingPythonCore"

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:3
msgid "Python Wrapper Core Classes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:5
msgid ""
"This directory provides the core support classes that are used by VTK's "
"Python wrappers.  The classes can be split into two broad categories: the "
"*PyVTK* classes provide C APIs for Python types, while the *vtkPython* "
"classes are C++ utility classes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:10
msgid "The Python Classes"
msgstr "Python 類別"

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:12
msgid "PyVTKObject"
msgstr "PyVTKObject"

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:14
msgid ""
"This defines APIs for creating and managing *PyVTKClass* objects, which are "
"Python extension types that wrap vtkObjectBase-derived classes, and "
"*PyVTKObject* objects, which are instances of the these extension types."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:18
msgid "PyVTKSpecialObject"
msgstr "PyVTKSpecialObject"

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:20
msgid ""
"Similarly, *PyVTKSpecialType* objects are Python extension types that wrap C+"
"+ classes that are *not* derived from vtkObjectBase, and "
"*PyVTKSpecialObject* wraps the instances.  These object are reference "
"counted on the Python side, but not on the C++ side.  In general they are "
"lightweight objects that are cheap to copy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:26
msgid "PyVTKTemplate"
msgstr "PyVTKTemplate"

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:28
msgid ""
"These objects represent C++ class templates.  The wrappers instantiate the "
"templates over a limited set of template parameters, and *PyVTKTemplate* is "
"a container for the template instantiations.  It is implemented as a "
"dictionary that maps template parameters to template instantiations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:33
msgid "PyVTKEnum"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:35
msgid ""
"This provides an API for managing subtypes of the Python *int* type that "
"represent named C++ enum types."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:38
msgid "PyVTKNamespace"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:40
msgid ""
"This provides an API for managing subtypes of the Python *module* type that "
"represent C++ namespaces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:43
msgid "PyVTKReference"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:45
msgid ""
"Python does not support C++-style pass-by-reference, but pass-by-reference "
"can be simulated by passing a typed container whose contents can be "
"modified. The *PyVTKReference* type defines such containers.  Within Python, "
"this type can be accessed as *vtkmodules.vtkCommonCore.reference*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:50
msgid "PyVTKMethodDescriptor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:52
msgid ""
"In Python, a method descriptor is an object that customizes method lookup, "
"specifically it customizes *object.method* and *class.method* method access. "
"The *PyVTKMethodDescriptor* customizes the access of *PyVTKClass* methods. "
"It handles bound method calls, unbound method calls, static method calls, "
"and calls to overloaded methods."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:58
msgid "PyVTKExtras"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:60
msgid ""
"This one is not actually a class, it is a helper function that adds utility "
"methods and types like the previously-mentioned *reference* type to the "
"vtkCommonCore module.  Everything in this file becomes part of vtkCommonCore."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:65
msgid "The C++ Classes"
msgstr "C++ 類別"

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:67
msgid "vtkPythonUtil"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:69
msgid ""
"This is a singleton that keeps track of all the vtk-python extension modules "
"that have been loaded, and all of the vtk-python objects that have been "
"instantiated.  It contains all of the machinery that is needed for moving "
"VTK objects from C++ to Python and back again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:74
msgid "vtkPythonCommand"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:76
msgid ""
"This is a subclass of vtkCommand that allows Python methods to be used as "
"VTK observer callbacks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:79
msgid "vtkPythonArgs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:81
msgid ""
"When a method call is performed in the wrappers, vtkPythonArgs does the "
"conversion of the arguments from Python to C++, and it also converts the "
"return value from C++ to Python."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:85
msgid "vtkPythonOverload"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:87
msgid ""
"When an overloaded method is called from Python, this class uses the method "
"arguments to decide which overload to use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:90
msgid "vtkPythonCompatibility"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:92
msgid ""
"This is actually just a header, not a class.  It contains macros that make "
"it easier to write code that is compatible with different versions of the "
"Python C API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:96
msgid "vtkSmartPyObject"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Wrapping/PythonCore/README.md:98
msgid ""
"Whereas the other classes in this directory are for using VTK C++ objects "
"through Python, this class is for using Python objects through C++.  This "
"class is a C++ smart pointer that handles Python reference counting."
msgstr ""
